-- Bernanke Says Fed Policies Benefit Housing, Auto Industries
-- B y   C a r o l i n e   S a l a s   G a g e
-- 2013-02-27T15:52:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-27/bernanke-says-fed-policies-benefit-housing-auto-industries.html
Federal Reserve Chairman Ben S.
Bernanke said the central bank’s easing policies are helping to
improve demand for housing and cars.  “We are getting some traction in the housing market, in
automobiles and other durable goods” and to “some extent in
investment” and commercial real estate, Bernanke said in
 Washington  today in response to questions from members of the
House Financial Services Committee.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Chris Wellisz at 
 cwellisz@bloomberg.net  